  "silentNoOpAudit": {
    "finding": "100% SILENT NO-OP \u2014 kelly-fraction flag is silently ignored by parseArgs() in run-hybrid-kelly.ts",
    "evidence": [
      "12 backtests run with --kelly-fraction \u2208 {0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 1.0}",
      "All 12 produced byte-identical equityCurveSampled (131 entries each per symbol)",
      "All 12 produced byte-identical walkForward.folds (24 folds each per symbol)",
      "All 12 produced byte-identical withHybridKelly.hybridSizer (avgKellyFraction=0.4156 BTC, etc.)",
      "All 12 produced byte-identical winRatePct, maxDrawdownPct, totalTrades, sharpeRatio",
      "Only monthlyReturnPct differs \u2014 by 1e-8 (sub-noise, from endTime=Date.now() drift)",
      "phase23-hybrid-kelly-0.5-btc-1d.json (with --kelly-fraction=0.5) is BYTE-IDENTICAL to baseline-hybrid-kelly-btc-1d.json (no flag)",
      "Root cause: run-hybrid-kelly.ts parseArgs() does NOT have a --kelly-fraction branch (only --symbol, --timeframe, --equity, --base-notional, --leverage, --output). Unknown flags silently ignored.",
      "Hardcoded baseKellyFraction: 0.5 (line 225 of run-hybrid-kelly.ts) is what runs every time",
      "Reproduces Phase 20 #1's negative finding from a different angle: the CLI does NOT support --kelly-fraction as a configurable parameter"
    ],
